Former president Jacob Zuma's latest court appearance shows he is not giving up. JOHANNESBURG - Former president Jacob Zuma is known for his Stalingrad legal tactics. But his lawyer says he's been ready to face corruption charges for 14 years. Zuma's latest court appearance shows he is not giving up. READ: Zuma says charges a 'political conspiracy' He plans to appeal Friday’s ruling dismissing his bid to halt the corruption case, forever. Zuma's future depends on a favourable Supreme Court of Appeal ruling or proving his innocence during trial.